spreadsheet.SUM: Sums all values, cell references or ranges.
spreadsheet.SUMIFS: Sums the cells specified by a given set of conditions or criteria.
spreadsheet.ABS: Returns the absolute value of a number.
spreadsheet.RAND: Return a random number between 0 and 1.
spreadsheet.FLOOR: Returns the round a number down to the nearest multiple of significance.
spreadsheet.CEILING: Returns a number rounded up to a nearest multiple of significance.
spreadsheet.SUMIF: It will sum up cells that meet the given criteria.
spreadsheet.PRODUCT: Multiplies all the numbers given as arguments and returns the product.
spreadsheet.AVERAGE: The sum of the numbers divided by how many numbers are being averaged.
spreadsheet.AVERAGEIF: Computes the average of the numbers in a range that meet the supplied criteria.
spreadsheet.COUNT: Counts the numbers in the list of arguments, exclude text entries.
spreadsheet.COUNTA: Counts the non-empty values in the list of arguments.
spreadsheet.COUNTIF: Counts the number of cells in a range that meet a specified condition.
spreadsheet.COUNTIFS: Counts the number of times each cells in all the ranges that meet the specific conditions.
spreadsheet.AVERAGEA: Calculates the average of values in the list of arguments.Arguments can be numbers, names, arrays or references.
spreadsheet.AVERAGEIFS: Conditionally returns the average of the contents of cells for the set of ranges.
spreadsheet.MIN: Returns the smaller number in set of arguments.
spreadsheet.MAX: Returns the largest number in set of arguments.
spreadsheet.DATE: Returns the date, given the year, month and day of the month.
spreadsheet.DAY: Returns the day of a given date.
spreadsheet.DAYS: Returns the number of days between two dates.
spreadsheet.IF: Returns one value if a logical expression is TRUE and another if it is FALSE
spreadsheet.AND: Returns TRUE if all the arguments are considered TRUE, and FALSE otherwise.
spreadsheet.IFS: Checks multiple conditions and returns a value corresponding to the first TRUE result.
spreadsheet.IFERROR: Returns a value you specify if a formula evaluates to an error; otherwise, it returns the result of the formula.
spreadsheet.CHOOSE: Returns a value from a list, given an index number.
spreadsheet.INDEX: Returns a value from a table, given a row and column number.
spreadsheet.FIND: Returns the position of a string of text within another string.
spreadsheet.CONCATENATE: Used to join two or more strings together.
spreadsheet.CONCAT: Concatenates a list or range of text strings.
spreadsheet.SUBTOTAL: Returns a subtotal in a list or database.
spreadsheet.OR: Returns TRUE if any arguments considered TRUE, and all the arguments are FALSE it will return FALSE.
spreadsheet.MATCH: Returns the relative position of an checked item in range that matches a specified value in a specified order.
spreadsheet.DefineNameExists: This name is already exists, try different name.
